Data Engineer
This data expert will be critical in implementing a new data strategy and architecture, including design standards and patterns, to develop Washington Federal’s data environments into a highly valued business asset supporting the dynamic data and analytics needs and data layer for application integration, leveraging appropriate data platforms and technologies.

Basic Responsibilities
Build, test and maintain cloud data pipelines from data sources, both on-prem and in-cloud, into AWS;
Design, build, test and maintain new data models and data marts;
Design, build and test and maintain data pipelines that move data, either large or small volume, into or out of data hub;
Own data quality of the data pipelines, data models and data marts;
Own, troubleshoot and build alert mechanics on issues in data pipelines and data hub;
Design and develop new systems and tools to enable users to consume and understand data faster;
Design and build data security rules, with encryption, masking and obfuscation, that protect customer data and ensure compliance;
Work with multiple teams to understand data requirements and build data solutions that can optimally support application integration, analytics and large data processing needs;
Can code in various languages, such as Python, Shell scripting, SQL, Java, Scala;
Execute POC projects with vendors and tools as needed;
Required Experiences and Skills
3+ years of ETL/ELT development experiences in Cloud environment;
3+ years of scripting and programming skills in linux environment;
3+ years of working with relational database;
2+ years of experiences working with open source ETL/ELT tools like Pentaho, Talend, Segment, Matillion;
2+ years of experiences working with big data technology and build scalable and complex data pipeline to deliver big data;
Desired Experiences and Skills
experiences working with columnar-stored relational database like Snowflake, Redshift;
experiences with designing and implementing cloud data security at transit and at rest;
experiences with designing and implementing several layers of role-based data access control in data hub;
experiences with designing, building and implementing virtual data warehouse;
having knowledge and / or experiences in modern cloud data platform with components of raw data storage, virtual data models, semantic data layers, data governance and micro services;
experiences working with orchestration tools like Airflow;
experiences working with Github, Docker;

